'''Zé''' ([[International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]] /{{IPA|zɛ}}/) in [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] is a common short form of the name "José".
([[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] ''José'', [[Pronunciation|pron.]] [[International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]] /{{IPA|'''ʒu'zɛ'''}}/).

Note that in [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] a "J" is pronounced as a {{IPA|[[ʒ]]}} and never as {{IPA|[[h]]}}.

'''Zé''' is to "José" as Joe is to Joseph.